description.narrative: Countries prioritized by the Global Strategy for Women's and Children's Health supported to define, adopt, finance, and operate health systems that deliver evidence-based, high impact interventions on an, which contributes to Child Health, Early Childhood Development, Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Technical expertise and management support provided to all UNICEF work streams for the equitable achievement of the MDGs by 2015, realizing the rights of every child in humanitarian and development contexts
